1. Requirements
 - postgresql >= 8.2 (even for compiling)
 - ocaml
 - ocamlduce
 - ocsigen and eliom with compiled ocamlduce support
 - pgocaml with lwt support
 - ocamlpam (recommended)

2. Run 

sh configure <password>

   where password is the password for database user ocsimore (see below).

   If you do not have ocamlpam installed, set PAM to NO in Makefile.config


3. Create a postgresql user with that name (here ocsimore) 
and a database called ocsimore:

sudo -u postgres createuser -P ocsimore
sudo -u postgres createdb -E UTF-8 -O ocsimore ocsimore

Adapt /etc/postgresql/.../pg_hba.conf to give Ident access for user ocsimore
by copying the following line (no modification needed):
local ocsimore ocsimore password

Restart postgresql, for example:
sudo /etc/init.d/postgresql restart

Then do:
psql -U ocsimore -f createdb.sql ocsimore
psql -U ocsimore -f user_createdb.sql ocsimore
psql -U ocsimore -f forum_createdb.sql ocsimore
psql -U ocsimore -f wiki_createdb.sql ocsimore

If something goes wrong, you can delete the database by typing:
sudo -u postgres dropdb ocsimore

4. Install pgocaml with lwt support (lwt branch of cvs)
http://merjis.com/developers/pgocaml

5. Compile ocsimore
make depend
make

6. Write and compile your site
or use example.ml:
make example.cmo

7. Adapt your ocsigen.conf using ocsigen.conf.example

8. Create a file containing the database password 
   (at the position set in the config file) and give right access
   only to Ocsigen's process user.

9. Run Ocsigen


